author: cmpilato
msg: Teach 'svnadmin setlog' to use the repository rev-prop-change hooks,
but provide an option for routing around those (in case the
administrator doesn't want to permit such changes via the client, for
example).
* subversion/svnadmin/main.c
(svnadmin__bypass_hooks, options_table, cmd_table, struct
svnadmin_opt_state, main): Add handling for new "--bypass-hooks"
option for 'svnadmin setlog'.
(subcommand_setlog): Now use the libsvn_repos interface for changing
revision properties, unless the --bypass-hooks option is passed,
in which case fall back to the old "hit-the-FS-directly" approach.
* subversion/contrib/cgi/tweak-log.cgi
(gBypassRevpropHooks): New global config option.
(doCommitLog): Maybe pass --bypass-hooks to the 'svnadmin setlog' command.
